ned the new field of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Quasicrystal\" title=\"Quasicrystal\">quasiperiodic crystals<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-discovery_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Dan_Shechtman#cite_note-discovery-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> Shechtman was awarded the 2011 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_in_Chemistry\" title=\"Nobel Prize in Chemistry\">Nobel Prize in Chemistry<\/a> for \"the discovery of quasicrystals,\" making him one of six Israelis who have won the Nobel Prize in Chemistry.<sup id=\"cite_ref-newswise1_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Dan_Shechtman#cite_note-newswise1-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Dan_Shechtman#cite_note-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Dan_Shechtman#cite_note-5\"><span>[<\/span>5<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Dan_Shechtman#cite_note-6\"><span>[<\/span>6<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Dan Shechtman","place_of_birth":"Tel Aviv, Israel","place_of_death":null,"text":"Dan Shechtman , Chemistry, 2011","year":2011.0}